===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym|眔|no_img=y}}
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|衣|眔|c1=s|c2=p|t1=clothes|ls=psc}}. Its original meaning is "to miss". The sadness linked to the act of missing is conveyed by the inside component 眔, an eye with tear under it; hence, the phonetic component also adds meaning to the character.{{rfv-etym|zh}} The dress is a reference to the bosom and/or the heart and mind. The character was later modified into [[懷]].

